<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bard</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Lcea's Lament (17 HP and 18 Mana/tick , AE) vs Chorus of Marr ( 20 HP and 21 Mana/tick, AE).<br>
Ancinet Lullaby of Shadow (Mez, 59 cap w/ 40% memblur, -1000 resist mod) vs Lullaby of Morell (Mez, 68 cap, no memblur, no resist mod)<br>
<br>
1 is clearly replaced, the other is situationally replaced.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Cleric</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Gift of Aegolism : (1300 HP, 69 AC, group) vs Hand of Virtue (1405 HP, 72 AC)<br>
Ancient High Priest's Bulwark : (350 HP, 30 AC, 7 Mana/tick, self only) vs Armor of the Zealot (450 HP, 36 AC, 8 Mana/tick, self only)<br>
<br>
Both are completely replaced.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Enchanter</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Chaotic Visions (950 point magic nuke, efficiency = 3.8)  vs Insanity (1100 magic nuke, efficiency = 3.67)<br>
Ancient Eternal Rapture (Mez, 61 cap, 40% memblur, -1000 resist check, 7 ticks) vs Sleep (Mez, 65 cap, 35% memblur, -10 resist, 9 ticks) or Bliss (Mez, 68 cap, 40% blur, -10 check, 9 ticks).<br>
<br>
Both are situationaly replaced.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wizard</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Greater Concusion (-600 hate) vs no PoP version.<br>
Ancient Destruction of Ice (1200 Ice nuke, -10 resist, eff= 4.8)  vs no PoP version.<br>
<br>
Neither is replaced.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Druid</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Starfire of Ro (1175 Fire nuke, eff =4.12) vs Summer's Flame (1400 fire nuke, eff = 3.94)<br>
Ancient Legacy of Blades (34 point group DS, 12 mins) vs Legacy of Bracken (40 point group DS, 6.5 mins)<br>
<br>
1 replaced situationally, 1 fully.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Necromancer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Master of Death (44 mana, 63 HP lich form) vs Seduction of Saryn (50 mana, 63 HP lich form)<br>
Ancient Lifebane (1050 poison nuke, eff=3.09) vs Neurotoxin (1400 poison nuke, eff = 2.80)<br>
<br>
1 total replaced, 1 situationally<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shaman</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Feral Avatar (+ 120 ATK/STR/DEX/AGI ) vs Ferine Avatar (+ 140 ATK/STR/DEX/AGI)<br>
Ancient Scourge of Nife (Poison DoT, 177 initial, 254/tick, 7 ticks) vs Blood of Saryn (Poison DoT, no initial, 320/tick, 7 ticks)<br>
<br>
Avatar situationaly replaced (you may want to have more than 2 melees avatared, in which case you would use both), Shaman DoT are not totally replaced as they can stack as many different dots as they want to on a mob, limited only by agro and number of effects possible on the mob.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Magician</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :<br>
Ancient Burnout Blaze : (AC 22, Str 80, Haste 80%, ATK 40) vs BO5 (AC 22, Str 80, Haste 85%, ATK 40)<br>
Ancient Shock of Sun (1150 fire nuke, eff = 4.04) vs Sun Vortex (1550 fire nuke, eff = 3.92)<br>
<br>
1 totaly replace, 1 situationally replaced.<br>
<br>
<br>
Pleas note that I consider the various nuke to be situationally replaced as there are times where size matters (nuke down mob X ASAP or we lose) and there are times where efficiency is paramount. The ancient nukes aren't as big as the PoP nukes but they are more efficient.<br>
<br>
I also only considered nukes with the same resist checks - an upgraded magic nuke doesn't help you on mobs where you need fire resist and vice-versa.<br>
<br>
Anyway, out of the 16 Ancient spells in the game I figure that<br>
6 are totaly replaced by PoP spells,  8 are replaced at least situationally, and 2 are never replaced (the 2 wizard ancients).<br>
<br>
As a result, I don't feel that there is anything out of line about BO5 being better than the ancient BO.<br>
<br>
